definition[0]: to do something better than someone else or be more successful
example[0]: We outstripped all our competitors in sales last year.
definition[1]: to be greater in quantity than something else
example[1]: Demand for new aircraft production is outstripping supply.
definition[2]: to run or move faster than someone or something else
example[2]: Speeding at 90 mph, Denny outstripped police cars for an hour.
